title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 1876 "Centennial Model" Rifle
postcontent: This is an original, Winchester Model 1876 Rifle made in 1884 and chambered for the .40-60 Winchester Center Fire cartridge. These rifles came to be known as the "Centennial Model" after their introduction in 1876. The '76 was a scaled up version of the Model 1873. It is very similar in appearance, but much larger. It was designed to compete with the big bore single shot rifles like the Sharps that were dominating the harvest of big game like the buffalo. This was the first Winchester lever action that allowed the use of true big game cartridges
